      "index": "aG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1111587468,
      "version": 169,
      "versionNonce": 43023028,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773920959328,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "HumanFeedbackResult\n\nThe HumanFeedbackResult \ndataclass contains all information about a human feedback interaction",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "HumanFeedbackResult\n\nThe HumanFeedbackResult \ndataclass contains all information about a human feedback interaction",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "y5qLRy9hg78oyJYzAU6-P",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 73.9149169921875,
      "y": 1648.4808484536645,
      "width": 478.699462890625,
      "height": 162,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1886727820,
      "version": 136,
      "versionNonce": 2088237876,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773920957972,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "@listen(\"approved\")\ndef on_approval(self, result: HumanFeedbackResult):\n    print(f\"Original output: {result.output}\")\n    print(f\"User feedback: {result.feedback}\")\n    print(f\"Outcome: {result.outcome}\")  # \"approved\"\n    print(f\"Received at: {result.timestamp}\")",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "@listen(\"approved\")\ndef on_approval(self, result: HumanFeedbackResult):\n    print(f\"Original output: {result.output}\")\n    print(f\"User feedback: {result.feedback}\")\n    print(f\"Outcome: {result.outcome}\")  # \"approved\"\n    print(f\"Received at: {result.timestamp}\")",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
      "id": "OvdOLnUN1MNkuDZWL1_fR",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 56.40193176269531,
      "y": 1081.1848366392996,
      "width": 1446.01806640625,
      "height": 351,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aI",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 362883724,
      "version": 56,
      "versionNonce": 1209748788,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773920960670,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "So now whatever the user types here, for example:\n\nTypes \"looks good, approve it\" → LLM maps → \"approved\" → @listen(\"approved\") triggers\n\nTypes \"this is wrong, reject\" → LLM maps → \"rejected\" → @listen(\"rejected\") triggers\n\nTypes \"add more examples please\" → LLM maps → \"needs_revision\" → @listen(\"needs_revision\")\ntriggers\n\nJust hits Enter → default_outcome kicks in → \"needs_revision\" → @listen(\"needs_revision\") triggers\n\nThe LLM (gpt-4o-mini in your case) is what does the smart mapping — so even natural language like \"yeah this looks fine\" gets correctly mapped to \"approved\".\n The user doesn't need to type the exact emit keyword.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 6,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "So now whatever the user types here, for example:\n\nTypes \"looks good, approve it\" → LLM maps → \"approved\" → @listen(\"approved\") triggers\n\nTypes \"this is wrong, reject\" → LLM maps → \"rejected\" → @listen(\"rejected\") triggers\n\nTypes \"add more examples please\" → LLM maps → \"needs_revision\" → @listen(\"needs_revision\")\ntriggers\n\nJust hits Enter → default_outcome kicks in → \"needs_revision\" → @listen(\"needs_revision\") triggers\n\nThe LLM (gpt-4o-mini in your case) is what does the smart mapping — so even natural language like \"yeah this looks fine\" gets correctly mapped to \"approved\".\n The user doesn't need to type the exact emit keyword.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.35
    },
    {
